<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="keywords" content="BOATS, Rights of Way" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>DDB0261</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Peter and Janet Young – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Regarding the above legislation which I understand is being scrutinised at present I wish to state that: My wife and I have witnessed  the damage caused by recreational vehicles being driven on the green lanes in the Yorkshire Dales, and we believe that this is a problem which exists in other parts of the country.  We know that damage caused by these vehicles does not heal quickly.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We agree whole heartedly with the proposal to re-classify all unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATs) an all unsealed Unclassified County Roads (UCRs) as Restricted Byways.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">These two categories of BOATs and UCRs should be recognised as not part of the ordinary roads network.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Traffic Regulation Orders (TROs):</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> I feel there should be a right of appeal against a local authority which declines to impose a TRO which is widely supported by the public.  The appeal should be to an independent inspector, or a magistrate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I am a member of the Yorkshire Dales Green Lanes Alliance (YDGLA) and fully support the formal submissions made by this organisation along with others.  These are the Green Lanes Environmental Action Group (GLPG), the Green Lanes Protection Group (GLPG), </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> Peak District Green Lanes Alliance (PDGLA).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">My wife also supports the above proposals and adds her signature.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">2 September 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>